text.section:
The term "capital improvements" as used in this section is limited to additions or improvements of a substantial and permanent nature and services rendered in connection therewith, and includes but is not limited to:
The purchase of rights of way for highways, expressways, and the widening of existing streets;
The purchase of lands for park, recreational, and other governmental facilities and for public off-street parking facilities;
The purchase, construction, reconstruction, renovation, or remodeling of municipal buildings, and facilities;
The replacement of machinery, wires, pipes, structural members or fixtures, and other essential portions of municipal buildings;
The initial equipment of any newly acquired facility wherein any essential governmental function of the municipality may be located or carried on;
The purchase and installation of traffic control devices and fire alarm equipment;
The reconstruction and resurfacing, but not routine maintenance, of streets and other public ways;
The acquisition of motorized equipment purchased as additions to, but not replacements for, existing equipment; and
Engineering and other costs incurred by the city in connection with the construction of public improvements financed under a special assessment plan.
